    "tagline": "Gateway to Africa, Mediterranean soul",
    "highlights": "[\"The Medina & Kasbah\",\"Cape Spartel & Caves of Hercules\",\"Grand Socco\",\"American Legation Museum\",\"Tangier Beach & Corniche\"]",
    "coords": "35.7595° N, 5.8340° W"
  },
  {
    "id": "ouarzazate",
    "name": "Ouarzazate",
    "description": "Ouarzazate is the gateway to the Sahara Desert and the film capital of Morocco. Known as the 'Hollywood of Morocco,' this oasis city is surrounded by stunning kasbahs, dramatic desert landscapes, and has served as the filming location for countless blockbuster movies including Gladiator, Lawrence of Arabia, and Game of Thrones.",
    "image": "/images/split_ruins.jpg",
    "category": "desert",
    "featured": false,
    "sort_order": 9,
    "created_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.694Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.694Z",
    "tagline": "Hollywood of Morocco, desert gateway",
    "highlights": "[\"Ait Ben Haddou UNESCO Kasbah\",\"Atlas Film Studios\",\"Taourirt Kasbah\",\"Cinema Museum\",\"Gateway to Sahara Desert\"]",
    "coords": "30.9196° N, 6.8936° W"
  },
  {
    "id": "meknes",
    "name": "Meknes",
    "description": "One of Morocco's four imperial cities, Meknes was the capital under Sultan Moulay Ismail in the 17th century. Known for its monumental gates, vast granaries, and royal stables, Meknes offers a more relaxed and authentic experience than its busier counterparts, with stunning architecture and a rich history.",
    "image": "/images/split_architecture.jpg",
    "category": "cities",
    "featured": false,
    "sort_order": 10,
    "created_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.834Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.834Z",
    "tagline": "Imperial grandeur, royal heritage",
    "highlights": "[\"Bab Mansour Gate\",\"Moulay Ismail Mausoleum\",\"Heri es-Souani granaries\",\"Place el-Hedim\",\"Volubilis nearby Roman ruins\"]",
    "coords": "33.8950° N, 5.5547° W"
  },
  {
    "id": "zagora",
    "name": "Zagora",
    "description": "Zagora sits on the edge of the Sahara Desert, marking the last major settlement before the vast dunes of the south. Known for the famous sign 'Timbuktu 52 days,' this frontier town is the starting point for camel treks into the desert and offers a genuine taste of southern Moroccan desert culture.",
    "image": "/images/dest_zagora.jpg",
    "category": "desert",
    "featured": false,
    "sort_order": 11,
    "created_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.969Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-29T01:09:46.969Z",
    "tagline": "Desert frontier, palm oasis",
    "highlights": "[\"Timbuktu 52 Days Sign\",\"Draa Valley palm groves\",\"Desert camel treks\",\"Tamegroute village & library\",\"M'hamid Erg Chigaga gateway\"]",
    "coords": "30.3480° N, 5.8388° W"
  },
  {
    "id": "errachidia",
    "name": "Errachidia",
    "description": "Errachidia is a strategic crossroads town in southeastern Morocco, serving as the gateway between the Middle Atlas mountains and the Sahara Desert. Overlooking the stunning Ziz Valley with its vast palm oasis, Errachidia is an important stop on the route to Merzouga and the Erg Chebbi dunes.",
    "image": "/images/dest_errachidia.jpg",
